the Miss Universe contest.

718
00:53:33,121 --> 00:53:37,280
Health officials from around the world are
concerned that the message from Vega...

719
00:53:37,440 --> 00:53:39,959
...might trigger a rash of mass suicides...

720
00:53:40,160 --> 00:53:42,679
...not unlike the recent cult deaths
near San Diego...

721
00:53:42,880 --> 00:53:44,759
Even a scientist has to admit...

722
00:53:44,960 --> 00:53:49,278
...that there are some pretty serious
religious overtones to all this.

723
00:53:49,439 --> 00:53:51,519
Let's hear from someone
whose organization...

724
00:53:51,719 --> 00:53:54,159
...has been accused of conducting
its own inquisition:

725
00:53:54,319 --> 00:53:56,838
Richard Rank,
head of the Conservative coalition.

726
00:53:56,999 --> 00:53:58,038
Thank you.

727
00:53:58,199 --> 00:54:02,397
This is yet another example of science
intruding into matters of faith.

728
00:54:03,398 --> 00:54:06,557
This means they
have been reacting to TV signals...

729
00:54:06,759 --> 00:54:09,557
...they got from the 1930s.
They're just getting them.

730
00:54:09,758 --> 00:54:13,277
Imagine how disappointed
they're gonna be if they're Cubs fans.

731
00:54:13,438 --> 00:54:16,477
We now take you to Jeremy Roth,
who is reporting on events...

732
00:54:16,677 --> 00:54:19,996
...at the Very Large Array
near Socorro, New Mexico.

733
00:54:20,198 --> 00:54:21,956
Like a bolt from the blue it came.

734
00:54:22,118 --> 00:54:26,116
The message from Vega has caused
thousands of believers and non-believers...

735
00:54:26,277 --> 00:54:30,036
...to descend upon the VLA facility
here in the desert of New Mexico.

736
00:54:30,236 --> 00:54:32,636
Many have come to protest,
many to pray...

737
00:54:32,797 --> 00:54:37,435
...but most have come to participate
in what has become the best show in town.

738
00:55:34,991 --> 00:55:40,630
That's right. I'll be there in Vega,
thank you very much.

739
00:55:43,511 --> 00:55:46,310
Hajl to Vega
Hail to Vega, Hail to Vega

740
00:55:46,471 --> 00:55:49,590
Hail to Vega

741
00:55:50,870 --> 00:55:52,469
But they have failed!

742
00:55:53,030 --> 00:55:55,469
It's the same people who,
again and again...

743
00:55:55,630 --> 00:55:57,949
...have brought us
to the brink of destruction.

744
00:55:58,149 --> 00:56:02,028
Who've polluted our air,
who've poisoned our water.

745
00:56:03,190 --> 00:56:05,109
Now these scientists...

746
00:56:06,069 --> 00:56:07,827
...have had their chance.

747
00:56:07,988 --> 00:56:11,267
Are these the kind of people...

748
00:56:11,428 --> 00:56:14,427
...that you want
talking to your God for you?

749
00:56:18,707 --> 00:56:20,706
Efforts continue around the clock.

750
00:56:21,028 --> 00:56:24,466
But for now, almost 2 full weeks
after the message's arrival...

751
00:56:24,627 --> 00:56:27,666
...scientists here at the VLA
still have no answers...

752
00:56:27,827 --> 00:56:29,506
...only more questions.

753
00:56:29,667 --> 00:56:33,226
Jeremy Roth, CNN,
Soccorro, New Mexico.

754
00:56:33,386 --> 00:56:36,585
More on the quest
for the message's meaning, after this.

755
00:56:39,306 --> 00:56:40,985
They gotta line up somehow.

756
00:56:41,146 --> 00:56:43,025
Yeah, well, this one doesn't fit, either.

757
00:56:43,186 --> 00:56:45,744
We've tried over a million permutations.

758
00:56:45,905 --> 00:56:49,265
Always, I can only get
three corners to fit.

759
00:56:50,226 --> 00:56:52,264
I don't understand their significance.

760
00:57:32,422 --> 00:57:35,020
What...? Somebody broke in...

761
00:57:41,101 --> 00:57:42,219
Hello?

762
00:57:43,101 --> 00:57:46,379
Hey, listen, I don't know who you are,
but you broke into the database...

763
00:57:49,100 --> 00:57:50,739
What? Now?

764
00:57:53,100 --> 00:57:54,219
Where?

765
00:58:06,699 --> 00:58:08,058
I'll be there.

766
00:58:34,537 --> 00:58:35,817
You should feel fortunate.

767
00:58:36,537 --> 00:58:37,976
He hardly lands for anyone.

768
00:59:08,254 --> 00:59:10,133
Dr. Arroway...

769
00:59:13,894 --> 00:59:15,173
...I presume?

770
00:59:16,414 --> 00:59:17,493
Mr. Hadden.

771
00:59:18,734 --> 00:59:21,852
I've had my eye on you
a long time, doctor.

772
00:59:22,613 --> 00:59:25,972
I consider you one of my
most valuable long-term investments.

773
00:59:27,773 --> 00:59:30,051
And when it comes to my investments...

774
00:59:31,773 --> 00:59:34,331
...I always do my homework.

775
00:59:38,852 --> 00:59:40,531
Eleanor Ann Arroway...

776
00:59:40,732 --> 00:59:43,131
...born 25th August, 1964...

777
00:59:43,331 --> 00:59:44,850
...De Pere, Wisconsin.

778
00:59:45,052 --> 00:59:49,090
Mother, Joanna, died
from complications during childbirth.

779
00:59:49,771 --> 00:59:52,370
Early testing indicated
high predisposition...

780
00:59:52,531 --> 00:59:55,490
...towards science and mathematics.

781
00:59:56,131 --> 00:59:57,250
Father, Theodore...

782
00:59:57,411 --> 01:00:00,810
...advised to provide
enrichment activities along these lines...

783
01:00:01,010 --> 01:00:03,649
...did so conscientiously
until his death...

784
01:00:03,810 --> 01:00:08,288
...from myocardial infarction,
November 10, 1974.

785
01:00:08,849 --> 01:00:11,967
You graduated from
high school in 1979...

786
01:00:12,128 --> 01:00:14,167
...almost two full years early.

787
01:00:15,528 --> 01:00:19,727
Awarded full scholarship, M.I. T,
graduated magna cum laude.

788
01:00:20,648 --> 01:00:22,287
Doctoral work, Cal Tech...

789
01:00:22,488 --> 01:00:25,686
...where you did breakthrough work
on the lanthanide-doped ruby maser...

790
01:00:25,847 --> 01:00:29,806
...dramatically increasing
the sensitivity of radio telescopes.

791
01:00:30,127 --> 01:00:33,686
Subsequently offered a teaching position
at Harvard University...

792
01:00:33,888 --> 01:00:36,846
...which you turned down
to pursue SETI work...

793
01:00:37,047 --> 01:00:40,326
...at the Arecibo Observatory
in Puerto Rico.

794
01:00:42,647 --> 01:00:48,262
Changes in NSF policy
gave rise to certain funding problems...

795
01:00:49,686 --> 01:00:53,524
...at which point
you came to my attention.

796
01:00:54,806 --> 01:00:56,925
You compromised our security codes.

797
01:00:59,285 --> 01:01:01,045
Once upon a time...

798
01:01:02,966 --> 01:01:05,124
...I was a hell of an engineer.

799
01:01:05,285 --> 01:01:07,604
Please, sit, doctor.

800
01:01:07,765 --> 01:01:12,684
I have guests so rarely, it's important to me
that they feel welcome in my home.

801
01:01:13,245 --> 01:01:14,923
You live here?

802
01:01:16,084 --> 01:01:19,284
I find it convenient
to keep my interests...

803
01:01:20,404 --> 01:01:21,483
...mobile.

804
01:01:23,963 --> 01:01:28,682
Anyway, I've had my fill
of life on the ground.

805
01:01:29,163 --> 01:01:31,202
Well, I... I guess I should...

806
01:01:31,642 --> 01:01:35,281
Well, I guess I should thank you
for having bailed me out all that time.

807
01:01:40,402 --> 01:01:42,441
I know a good bet when I see one.

808
01:01:44,721 --> 01:01:47,801
Earl Grey. No sugar, no milk, I believe.

809
01:01:50,641 --> 01:01:52,400
What am I doing here?

810
01:02:02,320 --> 01:02:05,319
The powers that be
have been very busy lately...

811
01:02:06,120 --> 01:02:11,239
...falling over each other to position
themselves for the game of the millennium.

812
01:02:17,239 --> 01:02:19,918
Maybe I can help deal you back in.

813
01:02:21,119 --> 01:02:23,438
I didn't realize that I was out.

814
01:02:23,919 --> 01:02:26,117
No, maybe not out...

815
01:02:26,798 --> 01:02:28,997
...but certainly being handed your hat.

816
01:02:34,198 --> 01:02:37,717
I've had a long time
to make enemies, doctor.

817
01:02:41,158 --> 01:02:44,837
And there are many governments,
business interests...

818
01:02:44,998 --> 01:02:48,836
...even religious leaders that
would like to see me depart this earth.

819
01:02:50,236 --> 01:02:52,675
And I'll grant them their wish
soon enough.

820
01:02:53,196 --> 01:02:56,595
But before I do,
I wish to make a small contribution.

821
01:02:57,316 --> 01:03:01,715
A final gesture of goodwill to the people
of this little planet that have given...

822
01:03:04,395 --> 01:03:07,074
From whom I have taken so much.

823
01:03:10,394 --> 01:03:11,793
You found the primer.

824
01:03:14,114 --> 01:03:15,913
Clever girl.

825
01:03:16,074 --> 01:03:17,074
Lights.

826
01:03:25,314 --> 01:03:28,352
Pages and pages of data.

827
01:03:28,513 --> 01:03:31,512
Over 63,000 in all.

828
01:03:31,673 --> 01:03:33,672
And on the perimeter of each...

829
01:03:33,833 --> 01:03:37,312
Alignment symbols, a registration mark,
but they don't line up.

830
01:03:37,873 --> 01:03:40,912
They do, if you think like a Vegan.

831
01:03:41,792 --> 01:03:44,671
An alien intelligence
has got be more advanced...

832
01:03:44,832 --> 01:03:48,751
...and that means efficiency
functioning on multiple levels...

833
01:03:48,912 --> 01:03:52,591
...and in multiple dimensions.

834
01:03:56,392 --> 01:03:58,710
Yes, of course!

835
01:03:58,872 --> 01:03:59,871
Where's the primer?

836
01:04:00,351 --> 01:04:01,710
You'll see.

837
01:04:02,191 --> 01:04:06,469
Every three-dimensional page
contains a piece of the primer.

838
01:04:08,549 --> 01:04:11,909
There it was all the time,
staring you in the face.

839
01:04:12,949 --> 01:04:16,708
Buried within the message itself
is the key to decoding it.

840
01:04:16,870 --> 01:04:19,988
Within the layering of the matrix,
we have these basic equations:

841
01:04:21,869 --> 01:04:25,748
So with this very elementary foundation,
they have given us a kind of...

842
01:04:25,909 --> 01:04:28,388
...general scientific vocabulary.

843
01:04:28,588 --> 01:04:30,787
We now have the symbols
for true and false...

844
01:04:30,989 --> 01:04:32,228
This was the key...

845
01:04:32,388 --> 01:04:34,787
...that allowed us
to decipher their language...

846
01:04:34,987 --> 01:04:38,507
...for physics, geometry, chemistry.
Next frame, Ellie.

847
01:04:39,667 --> 01:04:43,467
Yes, and when we apply this
to the rest of the message...

848
01:04:44,187 --> 01:04:45,226
...we find this.

849
01:04:49,627 --> 01:04:52,426
Those look like engineering schematics,
almost like blueprints.

850
01:04:52,587 --> 01:04:54,146
Yeah.

851
01:04:54,307 --> 01:04:55,346
Yes.

852
01:04:55,507 --> 01:04:58,666
It is our belief that
the message contains instructions...

853
01:04:58,866 --> 01:05:02,185
...for building something,
some kind of machine.

854
01:05:02,346 --> 01:05:05,345
A machine? That does what, doctor?

855
01:05:05,506 --> 01:05:07,624
We don't know.
It might be some type...

856
01:05:08,546 --> 01:05:13,864
...of advanced communication device,
or a teaching machine of some kind.

857
01:05:14,345 --> 01:05:17,504
Or it might turn out to be
some kind of a transport.

858
01:05:17,905 --> 01:05:20,264
- Transport?
- There's no proof of that.

859
01:05:20,425 --> 01:05:24,103
The fact is, you don't know what it does.
It could be anything.

860
01:05:24,264 --> 01:05:27,463
Could be a Trojan horse. We build it
and out pours the entire Vegan army.

861
01:05:27,624 --> 01:05:30,182
Why bother risking the personnel?
It could be a weapon.

862
01:05:30,383 --> 01:05:32,582
Right. Some kind of
a doomsday machine.

863
01:05:32,743 --> 01:05:35,142
Exactly. Every time they detect
a new civilization...

864
01:05:35,303 --> 01:05:37,661
...they fax these construction documents
from space.

865
01:05:37,822 --> 01:05:41,302
We poor saps build whatever this is
and blow ourselves to kingdom come.

866
01:05:41,463 --> 01:05:44,261
There's no reason to believe
that their intentions are hostile.

867
01:05:44,422 --> 01:05:48,581
Why is the default position of the egghead
set that aliens would always be benign?

868
01:05:48,742 --> 01:05:51,100
- Why is that, doctor?
- We pose no threat to them.

869
01:05:51,262 --> 01:05:55,500
It would be like us going out of our way
to destroy microbes on an anthill in Africa

870
01:05:55,661 --> 01:05:57,180
That's an interesting analogy.

871
01:05:57,581 --> 01:06:01,580
And how guilty would we feel if we
destroyed a few microbes on an anthill?

872
01:06:01,741 --> 01:06:04,020
I hope you're right, doctor. I really do.

873
01:06:04,181 --> 01:06:07,500
But right now my job is to protect
American lives from any threat.

874
01:06:07,661 --> 01:06:09,899
In that regard, I am obligated
to assume the worst.

875
01:06:10,141 --> 01:06:12,139
Well, yes, and I am forced
to agree with you.

876
01:06:12,301 --> 01:06:13,659
My problem is this:

877
01:06:14,261 --> 01:06:17,339
The content of that message
is morally ambiguous at best.

878
01:06:17,980 --> 01:06:21,379
Now, our internal numbers show
support for this is incredibly soft.

879
01:06:21,539 --> 01:06:24,099
If the president wishes
to stay this course...

880
01:06:24,260 --> 01:06:26,818
...you're gonna find his numbers
going south like a duck.

881
01:06:26,980 --> 01:06:29,298
- This is nuts.
- Excuse me...

882
01:06:29,459 --> 01:06:30,818
...miss.

883
01:06:30,979 --> 01:06:33,258
We know nothing
of these creatures' values.

884
01:06:33,419 --> 01:06:36,098
The fact is, we don't even know
whether they believe in God.

885
01:06:36,259 --> 01:06:39,858
- This doesn't make any sense. If you...
- Excuse me, Dr. Arroway.

886
01:06:40,058 --> 01:06:42,417
We won't be suppressing
any opinions here today.

887
01:06:43,258 --> 01:06:45,857
No, of course not.
I understand.

888
01:06:46,258 --> 01:06:48,096
What I meant to say...

889
01:06:48,257 --> 01:06:51,575
...is the message was written
in the language of science.

890
01:06:51,736 --> 01:06:54,976
Now, if it had been religious in nature,
it should have taken the form...

891
01:06:55,136 --> 01:06:57,655
...of a burning bush
or a booming voice from the sky.

892
01:06:57,857 --> 01:06:59,855
But a voice from the sky...

893
01:07:00,896 --> 01:07:03,615
...is exactly what you found,
Doctor Arroway.

894
01:07:06,856 --> 01:07:08,734
I'm sorry I'm late, ma'am.

895
01:07:08,895 --> 01:07:13,895
Now, I agree with Mr. Rank
that there are unavoidable...

896
01:07:14,095 --> 01:07:16,174
...religious implications at stake here.

897
01:07:16,335 --> 01:07:18,654
But that doesn't justify
taking an alarmist position.

898
01:07:20,615 --> 01:07:23,253
My hope here is that we can find
a common ground...

899
01:07:23,414 --> 01:07:26,013
...break through any obstacles
that may have kept us apart.

900
01:07:26,174 --> 01:07:29,453
- Well, perhaps...
- Listen, I need to make one thing very clear.

901
01:07:29,654 --> 01:07:34,093
Our organization will not be placated
with flowery New Age rhetoric...

902
01:07:35,053 --> 01:07:36,493
Mr. President.

903
01:07:37,894 --> 01:07:40,093
The President met
with his top advisors today...

904
01:07:40,253 --> 01:07:43,533
...regarding the latest efforts
to decode the message.

905
01:07:43,693 --> 01:07:48,172
While there has been some progress,
the official line remains a cautious one.

906
01:07:48,333 --> 01:07:52,771
If you're asking when we'll find out
what the purpose of that machine is...

907
01:07:53,732 --> 01:07:56,331
...maybe tomorrow,
maybe next year, maybe never.

908
01:08:00,572 --> 01:08:04,971
There he is. The man with his finger
on the spiritual pulse of the nation.

909
01:08:06,292 --> 01:08:09,570
- It's so good to see you, Ellie.
- You too.

910
01:08:10,770 --> 01:08:14,569
Your discovery, all of this.
It must be a real vindication.

911
01:08:15,211 --> 01:08:16,809
I'm really happy for you.

912
01:08:17,409 --> 01:08:21,209
- Are you?
- Mr. Joss, the president is waiting.

913
01:08:22,529 --> 01:08:25,528
- Okay. Yeah.
- The president is waiting.

914
01:08:29,289 --> 01:08:33,008
- Ellie, see you at the reception tonight?
- Yeah, I wouldn't miss it.

915
01:08:33,169 --> 01:08:34,967
All right, great.

916
01:08:44,568 --> 01:08:46,807
Excuse me, Miss Constantine,
may I speak to you?

917
01:08:46,968 --> 01:08:48,327
Certainly.

918
01:08:50,008 --> 01:08:52,126
- I have a big problem.
- Yes?

919
01:08:52,287 --> 01:08:53,727
Um...

920
01:08:53,887 --> 01:08:56,566
Do you know where I can find,
like, a really great dress?

921
01:09:12,566 --> 01:09:18,645
God created man in the form of himself,
not in the form of monkeys!

922
01:09:20,406 --> 01:09:22,485
- The Lord is God!
- Praise God.

923
01:09:22,646 --> 01:09:26,684
- Praise the Lord!
- You're wasting my tax dollars!

924
01:09:27,445 --> 01:09:30,923
Get a job.
Don't waste my tax dollars.

925
01:09:31,084 --> 01:09:32,763
You hear me?

926
01:09:50,962 --> 01:09:52,682
Wow.

927
01:09:55,122 --> 01:09:56,721
You look beautiful, Ellie.

928
01:09:58,322 --> 01:10:00,561
- So do you.
- You really do.

929
01:10:04,082 --> 01:10:05,480
I read your book.

930
01:10:06,402 --> 01:10:07,840
Here we go.

931
01:10:08,001 --> 01:10:10,000
Would you like me to quote you?

932
01:10:10,161 --> 01:10:14,960
"Ironically, the thing that people
are most hungry for, meaning...

933
01:10:15,121 --> 01:10:18,320
...is the one thing that science
hasn't been able to give them."

934
01:10:18,481 --> 01:10:21,239
Yeah. Yeah.

935
01:10:21,840 --> 01:10:26,440
Come on. It's like you're saying
that science killed God.

936
01:10:26,600 --> 01:10:29,679
What if science simply revealed...

937
01:10:29,840 --> 01:10:32,239
...that he never existed
in the first place?

938
01:10:35,440 --> 01:10:38,479
- I think we're gonna need to get some air.
- What?

939
01:10:38,640 --> 01:10:40,399
And a few more of these.

940
01:10:41,759 --> 01:10:43,918
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

941
01:10:44,879 --> 01:10:47,918
- A little chilly out here.
- Yeah, this is nice.

942
01:10:48,079 --> 01:10:49,397
- I got one for you.
- What?

943
01:10:49,558 --> 01:10:51,237
Occam's razor.
Ever heard of it?

944
01:10:51,437 --> 01:10:53,997
Hoccam's razor.
Sounds like some slasher movie.

945
01:10:54,157 --> 01:10:57,596
No, Occam's Razor.
It's a basic scientific principle. It says...

946
01:10:57,757 --> 01:11:01,196
...all things being equal, the simplest
explanation tends to be the right one.

947
01:11:01,357 --> 01:11:02,916
- Makes sense to me.
- All right.

948
01:11:03,076 --> 01:11:05,756
- So, what's more likely? Thank you.
- You're welcome.

949
01:11:05,917 --> 01:11:08,435
An all-powerful, mysterious God
created the universe...

950
01:11:08,637 --> 01:11:11,355
...and then decided not to give
any proof of his existence?

951
01:11:11,516 --> 01:11:16,155
Or that he simply doesn't exist at all
and that we created him...

952
01:11:16,316 --> 01:11:18,714
...so we wouldn't have to feel
so small and alone.

953
01:11:19,596 --> 01:11:20,794
I don't know.

954
01:11:20,956 --> 01:11:24,794
I couldn't imagine living in a world
where God didn't exist.

955
01:11:25,435 --> 01:11:27,034
I wouldn't want to.

956
01:11:27,675 --> 01:11:29,994
How do you know that
you're not deluding yourself?

957
01:11:30,634 --> 01:11:33,754
I mean, for me, I'd need proof.

958
01:11:34,555 --> 01:11:35,993
Proof?

959
01:11:38,754 --> 01:11:41,153
- Did you love your father?
- What?

960
01:11:41,315 --> 01:11:43,033
Your dad, did you love him?

961
01:11:43,994 --> 01:11:46,713
Yes. Very much.

962
01:11:49,433 --> 01:11:50,913
Prove it.

963
01:11:57,153 --> 01:11:58,152
Kent.

964
01:11:59,432 --> 01:12:02,311
- The White House.
- Mr. Joss.

965
01:12:03,432 --> 01:12:06,272
I don't want excuses.
Whoever is responsible, I want their head.

966
01:12:06,432 --> 01:12:09,271
- Ellie?
- What happened?

967
01:12:09,432 --> 01:12:10,791
You were right all along.

968
01:12:10,951 --> 01:12:13,950
The decryption team at the VLA
has been working around the clock...

969
01:12:14,111 --> 01:12:16,709
...and the hard work has finally paid off.

970
01:12:16,871 --> 01:12:20,670
This key section, uncovered tonight
and obtained exclusively by CNN...

971
01:12:20,830 --> 01:12:23,349
...shows an illustration
of what is of a human figure...

972
01:12:23,510 --> 01:12:26,229
...inside a geometric structure
of some kind.

973
01:12:26,390 --> 01:12:28,149
This and other contextual clues...

974
01:12:28,310 --> 01:12:31,269
...now lead scientists to believe
that the message is, in fact...

975
01:12:31,430 --> 01:12:34,828
- President called an emergency meeting.
- Yeah, I imagine he would.

976
01:12:34,989 --> 01:12:37,988
- Designed to take
a single human occupant into space...

977
01:12:38,149 --> 01:12:40,708
...presumably to the star Vega.

978
01:12:58,468 --> 01:13:00,347
I'm gonna miss
my mother's birthday party.

979
01:13:00,508 --> 01:13:03,267
Call her in the morning,
tell her why you didn't show up.

980
01:13:03,428 --> 01:13:04,866
Tell me.

981
01:13:05,027 --> 01:13:06,106
They're gonna build it.

982
01:13:06,267 --> 01:13:07,267
Who gets to go?

983
01:13:07,428 --> 01:13:10,626
The president's just gone international
to spread the risk and cost...

984
01:13:10,787 --> 01:13:12,266
Who gets to go, though?

985
01:13:12,427 --> 01:13:13,986
Well, it's complicated, Ellie.

986
01:13:14,866 --> 01:13:15,866
What?

987
01:13:16,027 --> 01:13:18,746
They have formed a group
of international candidates.

988
01:13:18,907 --> 01:13:20,866
Now, it's your discovery.

989
01:13:21,267 --> 01:13:24,986
Okay, they understand that.
You're at the top of a very short list.

990
01:13:25,146 --> 01:13:27,585
But they're also putting together
a selection committee.

991
01:13:27,746 --> 01:13:31,744
It's made of scholars, theologians,
scientists, philosophers...

992
01:13:31,905 --> 01:13:32,864
You're on it.

993
01:13:34,025 --> 01:13:35,264
I've been asked, yes.

994
01:13:38,104 --> 01:13:39,703
I guess that means...

995
01:13:40,264 --> 01:13:42,903
...that you're a selector,
I'm a selectee and we can't...

996
01:13:43,064 --> 01:13:44,343
Yeah.

997
01:13:44,504 --> 01:13:46,822
What you don't understand, Ellie, is...

998
01:13:46,984 --> 01:13:49,022
- I understand.
- Ellie...

999
01:13:49,624 --> 01:13:53,783
I want you to know, whatever happens,
as far as I'm concerned...

1000
01:13:54,343 --> 01:13:55,782
Well...

1001
01:13:56,903 --> 01:13:58,422
...good luck.

1002
01:14:02,263 --> 01:14:05,582
Well, whatever you do, make sure
he doesn't monopolize the committee.

1003
01:14:05,742 --> 01:14:07,742
He is not on the committee, Ellie.

1004
01:14:09,423 --> 01:14:10,781
What?

1005
01:14:11,542 --> 01:14:14,461
He just resigned as science advisor.
He wants to be the one to go.

1006
01:14:16,581 --> 01:14:19,740
The president is already
beginning to feel the financial pinch.

1007
01:14:20,021 --> 01:14:22,021
Sources say the cost of the project...

1008
01:14:22,181 --> 01:14:25,660
...is spiraling
to more than a third of a trillion dollars...

1009
01:14:25,821 --> 01:14:29,260
...making this what may be
the most expensive single project...

1010
01:14:29,460 --> 01:14:31,259
...in all of human history.

1011
01:14:31,461 --> 01:14:34,659
Meanwhile, months of debate finally
reached a conclusion last week...

1012
01:14:34,820 --> 01:14:37,819
...as 10 candidates
were selected by the IMC...

1013
01:14:37,980 --> 01:14:41,779
...representing a cross section of
political, philosophical and religious views.

1014
01:14:41,980 --> 01:14:44,739
Many of these are the same experts
who have been consulting...

1015
01:14:44,900 --> 01:14:46,859
...on the Machine's design and function.

1016
01:14:47,060 --> 01:14:51,098
They will be actively participating on-site
during the construction process.

1017
01:14:51,258 --> 01:14:54,457
But the choice of these 10 candidates
has not been without controversy.

1018
01:14:54,618 --> 01:14:57,337
Fully one-third of the candidates
are American.

1019
01:14:57,498 --> 01:15:00,137
Many international observers
are asking why.

1020
01:15:00,298 --> 01:15:03,297
The U.S. Is shouldering an
enormous percentage of the financial...

1021
01:15:03,497 --> 01:15:06,336
Isn't it true that the contractors,
like Hadden Industries...

1022
01:15:06,537 --> 01:15:09,736
...are making those contributions
in exchange for technology rights?

1023
01:15:09,937 --> 01:15:13,296
Different nations are being compensated
in different ways. For example...

1024
01:15:13,457 --> 01:15:17,816
Japan made headlines when it announced it
would forego candidate representation...

1025
01:15:17,977 --> 01:15:21,055
...in exchange for the systems integration
subcontract.

1026
01:15:21,216 --> 01:15:25,975
On what basis do you choose
a human being to represent humanity?

1027
01:15:26,176 --> 01:15:27,335
Good question, Larry.

1028
01:15:27,496 --> 01:15:29,374
Yes, well, if nothing else...

1029
01:15:29,535 --> 01:15:33,374
...it should be somebody who is fluent in
the language the message was given in.

1030
01:15:33,535 --> 01:15:34,695
Science, in this case.

1031
01:15:35,295 --> 01:15:37,614
Doctor Arroway,
despite your obvious enthusiasm...

1032
01:15:37,815 --> 01:15:39,934
...there's been a lot of criticism of late...

1033
01:15:40,175 --> 01:15:42,574
...that this whole endeavor
is simply too dangerous.

1034
01:15:42,735 --> 01:15:45,214
Some of that criticism from scientists.

1035
01:15:45,415 --> 01:15:48,094
One Nobel Prize winner recently noted,
his words:

1036
01:15:48,854 --> 01:15:50,493
"There is every indication...

1037
01:15:50,694 --> 01:15:54,333
"...that this is simply beyond our
capabilities, that this endeavor will fail..."

1038
01:15:54,534 --> 01:15:58,013
"...and that the Machine's occupant
will pay for that failure with their life."

1039
01:15:58,173 --> 01:15:59,773
How do you respond to that?

1040
01:15:59,973 --> 01:16:03,213
Well, this message is from
a civilization that may be anywhere...

1041
01:16:03,413 --> 01:16:06,972
...from hundreds to millions
and millions of years ahead of us.

1042
01:16:07,214 --> 01:16:10,251
I have to believe that
an intelligence that advanced...

1043
01:16:10,852 --> 01:16:12,771
...knows what they're doing.

1044
01:16:13,652 --> 01:16:17,451
Now all it requires on our part is...

1045
01:16:17,612 --> 01:16:18,610
Faith?

1046
01:16:21,571 --> 01:16:23,570
I was gonna say a sense of adventure.

1047
01:16:23,771 --> 01:16:24,930
And in breaking news...

1048
01:16:25,491 --> 01:16:26,730
...a former astronaut...

1049
01:16:26,931 --> 01:16:30,610
...considered to be the leading American
candidate for the Machine seat...

1050
01:16:30,810 --> 01:16:33,009
...has unexpectedly dropped out
of the running.

1051
01:16:33,411 --> 01:16:36,369
Russell met with reporters this afternoon
at his Houston home.

1052
01:16:36,691 --> 01:16:40,489
I told my dad
that I didn't want him to go.

1053
01:16:40,690 --> 01:16:42,328
Daddy, don't go.

1054
01:16:44,890 --> 01:16:47,848
Nothing would give me more pride
than to...

1055
01:16:48,490 --> 01:16:50,409
...represent my country.

1056
01:16:50,569 --> 01:16:52,688
But what can I say to this?

1057
01:16:53,249 --> 01:16:56,928
Consortium officials had no comment,
but sources within the delegation...

1058
01:16:57,089 --> 01:16:59,008
...have disclosed that Dr. Arroway...

1059
01:16:59,169 --> 01:17:03,087
...appears to now be the front-runner
for the Machine seat.

1060
01:17:03,888 --> 01:17:06,168
"Meet me at noon. Must talk."

1061
01:17:06,328 --> 01:17:08,967
I didn't expect to be getting
a message like this from you.

1062
01:17:09,128 --> 01:17:10,287
Thanks for coming.

1063
01:17:10,488 --> 01:17:13,326
So is this kosher?
Fraternizing with the enemy?

1064
01:17:13,487 --> 01:17:16,847
Selectors and selectees mingling around?

1065
01:17:17,008 --> 01:17:19,086
Can we talk about Einstein?

1066
01:17:19,247 --> 01:17:21,326
Yeah, sure. Okay.

1067
01:17:21,487 --> 01:17:22,846
- Special relativity.
- Yeah.

1068
01:17:23,007 --> 01:17:24,566
This machine...

1069
01:17:25,127 --> 01:17:29,845
...now, if it works, and you travel to Vega
at even close to the speed of light...

1070
01:17:30,006 --> 01:17:32,404
...when you come back...
- If you come back.

1071
01:17:34,485 --> 01:17:36,404
If you come back...

1072
01:17:36,565 --> 01:17:40,684
...you'll only be 4 years older, but over
50 years would have passed here on Earth.

1073
01:17:40,845 --> 01:17:42,484
Basically, yeah.

1074
01:17:42,964 --> 01:17:45,443
And everybody that you care about...

1075
01:17:46,284 --> 01:17:48,524
...will be gone, dead and buried.

1076
01:17:49,324 --> 01:17:53,163
If you came back,
if you survived at all, which...

1077
01:17:54,444 --> 01:17:58,003
Look, Palmer, nobody's saying
this isn't dangerous, all right?

1078
01:17:58,163 --> 01:18:02,123
The rest of the candidates and myself,
we fully understand the risks we're taking.

1079
01:18:02,283 --> 01:18:03,483
Why?

1080
01:18:03,644 --> 01:18:06,243
Because it's a historic opportunity.
The world needs...

1081
01:18:06,443 --> 01:18:08,962
No, you, Ellie.
You. You personally.

1082
01:18:09,963 --> 01:18:12,642
By doing this,
you're willing to give your life.

1083
01:18:12,842 --> 01:18:14,921
You're willing to die for it.

1084
01:18:16,682 --> 01:18:17,921
Why?

1085
01:18:21,482 --> 01:18:25,041
From as long as I can remember,
I've been searching for...

1086
01:18:25,642 --> 01:18:27,240
...something...

1087
01:18:27,442 --> 01:18:31,080
...some reason why we're here.
What are we doing here? Who are we?

1088
01:18:32,041 --> 01:18:35,760
If this is a chance to find out
even just a little part of that answer...

1089
01:18:37,201 --> 01:18:40,080
I don't know,
I think it's won'th a human life.

1090
01:18:40,721 --> 01:18:42,199
Don't you?

1091
01:18:48,440 --> 01:18:50,958
You're an incredibly brave woman, Ellie.

1092
01:18:53,639 --> 01:18:55,678
Or incredibly nuts.

1093
01:19:16,838 --> 01:19:18,276
Palmer...

1094
01:19:23,757 --> 01:19:25,756
I'm really confused.

1095
01:19:26,997 --> 01:19:28,196
So am I.

1096
01:19:29,396 --> 01:19:32,835
I think I speak for us all
when I thank you for your patience.

1097
01:19:33,037 --> 01:19:36,355
Myself, I have one final question,
Dr. Arroway.

1098
01:19:37,796 --> 01:19:40,035
If you should meet these Vegans...

1099
01:19:40,236 --> 01:19:44,355
...and were permitted only
one question to ask of them...

1100
01:19:44,516 --> 01:19:46,114
...what would it be?

1101
01:19:47,515 --> 01:19:49,474
Well, I suppose it would be:

1102
01:19:49,636 --> 01:19:51,234
"How did you do it?"

1103
01:19:51,755 --> 01:19:56,034
"How did you evolve? How did you
survive this technological adolescence..."

1104
01:19:56,195 --> 01:19:58,033
"...without destroying yourself?"

1105
01:19:58,754 --> 01:20:03,433
That more than any other question is one
I personally would like to have answered.

1106
01:20:03,755 --> 01:20:05,513
Not too bad, Mike.

1107
01:20:06,154 --> 01:20:07,393
I join Dr. Bergeron...

1108
01:20:07,554 --> 01:20:10,872
...in expressing thanks for
your patience, Dr. Arroway.

1109
01:20:11,073 --> 01:20:13,472
We've all been most impressed
with your candor...

1110
01:20:13,633 --> 01:20:15,591
...and your stamina.

1111
01:20:15,752 --> 01:20:18,791
I believe we are ready to move on
to your final statement.

1112
01:20:18,952 --> 01:20:20,791
Madam Chairman,
I have one more question.

1113
01:20:20,952 --> 01:20:22,631
Yes, Mr. Joss.

1114
01:20:23,232 --> 01:20:25,151
Dr. Arroway...

1115
01:20:26,472 --> 01:20:28,711
Would you consider yourself...

1116
01:20:29,191 --> 01:20:31,711
...a spiritual person?

1117
01:20:34,271 --> 01:20:35,950
Uh...

1118
01:20:36,671 --> 01:20:39,870
I don't really understand
the point of the question.

1119
01:20:40,031 --> 01:20:42,790
I consider myself a moral person.

1120
01:20:42,951 --> 01:20:44,829
I'm sure we all agree that is the case...

1121
01:20:44,991 --> 01:20:47,389
...but I think what Mr. Joss
is in fact asking...

1122
01:20:47,550 --> 01:20:49,309
Do you believe in God...

1123
01:20:51,230 --> 01:20:53,149
...Dr. Arroway?

1124
01:20:57,470 --> 01:20:59,789
As a scientist...

1125
01:20:59,950 --> 01:21:03,269
...I rely on empirical evidence,
and in this matter...

1126
01:21:03,429 --> 01:21:06,989
...I don't believe
that there is data either way.

1127
01:21:07,549 --> 01:21:11,788
So your answer would in fact be
that you don't believe in God.

1128
01:21:15,069 --> 01:21:17,987
I don't understand the relevance
of the question.

1129
01:21:18,668 --> 01:21:23,586
Dr. Arroway,
95 percent of the world's population...

1130
01:21:23,748 --> 01:21:27,547
...believes in a supreme being
in one form or another.

1131
01:21:28,667 --> 01:21:31,745
I believe that makes the question
more than relevant.

1132
01:21:34,306 --> 01:21:35,945
Dr. Arroway?

1133
01:21:45,465 --> 01:21:47,384
I believe, um...

1134
01:21:51,225 --> 01:21:53,623
I believe I've already
answered that question.

1135
01:21:57,504 --> 01:22:00,864
I'm proud of what
we've achieved as a species...

1136
01:22:01,024 --> 01:22:02,943
...and as a civilization.

1137
01:22:04,544 --> 01:22:06,943
I would hate to see
everything we stand for...

1138
01:22:07,104 --> 01:22:10,863
...all that we have fought for
for a thousand generations...

1139
01:22:11,063 --> 01:22:13,303
...all that God has blessed us with...

1140
01:22:14,584 --> 01:22:16,063
...betrayed...

1141
01:22:16,983 --> 01:22:21,382
...in the final hour because we chose to
send a representative who did not put our...

1142
01:22:21,863 --> 01:22:24,542
...most cherished beliefs first.

1143
01:22:27,703 --> 01:22:28,822
Thank you.

1144
01:23:00,699 --> 01:23:01,938
Why did you do it?

1145
01:23:06,339 --> 01:23:10,338
Our job was to select someone
to speak for everybody.

1146
01:23:13,499 --> 01:23:16,818
I just couldn't in good conscience
vote for a person...

1147
01:23:16,979 --> 01:23:18,898
...who doesn't believe in God.

1148
01:23:20,858 --> 01:23:22,177
Someone who...

1149
01:23:22,338 --> 01:23:25,617
...honestly thinks
the other 95 percent of us...

1150
01:23:25,818 --> 01:23:28,656
...suffer from some form
of mass delusion.

1151
01:23:31,697 --> 01:23:33,696
I told the truth up there.

1152
01:23:34,937 --> 01:23:38,296
And Drumlin told you exactly
what you wanted to hear.

1153
01:24:12,013 --> 01:24:14,492
With full humility and utmost gratitude...

1154
01:24:14,653 --> 01:24:16,773
...I accept this great honor...

1155
01:24:16,973 --> 01:24:20,852
...and I promise I will do my best
to represent my nation...

1156
01:24:21,013 --> 01:24:25,932
...my planet and my God
on this historic journey.

1157
01:24:26,093 --> 01:24:28,331
I thank you from the bottom of my heart.

1158
01:25:09,169 --> 01:25:12,009
There's
a carnival atmosphere at Cape Canaveral...

1159
01:25:12,170 --> 01:25:14,128
...as the International
Machine Consortium...

1160
01:25:14,289 --> 01:25:17,608
...hosts as much a media event
as a systems test.

1161
01:25:18,089 --> 01:25:21,608
David Drumlin is supervising
the on-site portion of the test.

1162
01:25:21,809 --> 01:25:23,528
We spoke with him earlier today.

1163
01:25:23,689 --> 01:25:26,087
We'll be able to monjtor
the stresses and effects...

1164
01:25:26,249 --> 01:25:28,488
...using the robot passenger...

1165
01:25:28,968 --> 01:25:31,167
...who we lovingly call Elmer.

1166
01:25:31,327 --> 01:25:34,326
We are coming up
on T-minus two hours and counting.

1167
01:25:34,487 --> 01:25:36,446
All Machine systems are go.

1168
01:25:36,606 --> 01:25:39,365
Dr. Arroway, the press would like to
ask you a few questions...

1169
01:25:39,527 --> 01:25:42,085
...as soon as they're done
with Dr. Drumlin.

1170
01:25:43,326 --> 01:25:45,486
Now, at the moment
where we release the pod...

1171
01:25:45,646 --> 01:25:49,085
...there will be a substantial
amount of energy generated at the core.

1172
01:25:49,566 --> 01:25:51,845
We'll be able to monitor
the stresses and effects...

1173
01:25:52,006 --> 01:25:56,005
...using our robot passenger,
who we lovingly call Elmer.

1174
01:25:57,445 --> 01:25:59,004
- Thank you.
- Welcome.

1175
01:25:59,165 --> 01:26:01,004
The test area is clear and go.

1176
01:26:01,165 --> 01:26:03,844
Sir, they're ready for you out at the site.

1177
01:26:04,005 --> 01:26:05,564
Yeah, just a minute.

1178
01:26:06,565 --> 01:26:09,724
The test director has issued a go
to enter the final countdown phase.

1179
01:26:09,885 --> 01:26:11,163
Ellie.

1180
01:26:11,324 --> 01:26:13,604
- Congratulations, David.
- Glad you could come.

1181
01:26:14,884 --> 01:26:17,243
Didrt, uh, expect to see you here.

1182
01:26:17,924 --> 01:26:22,563
Well, I'm still, you know,
Crew Ops at the Control Center.

1183
01:26:23,204 --> 01:26:27,043
And I suppose the fact that I discovered
the message means that I have PR value.

1184
01:26:27,203 --> 01:26:28,803
Of course.

1185
01:26:30,243 --> 01:26:33,282
Ellie, I know you must think
this is all very unfair.

1186
01:26:33,923 --> 01:26:36,121
And maybe that's an understatement.

1187
01:26:37,163 --> 01:26:39,441
What you don't know is, I agree.

1188
01:26:40,002 --> 01:26:43,161
I wish the world was a place
where fair was the bottom line.

1189
01:26:43,322 --> 01:26:46,401
Where the kind of idealism you showed
at the hearing was rewarded...

1190
01:26:46,562 --> 01:26:48,761
...not taken advantage of.

1191
01:26:50,402 --> 01:26:53,399
Unfortunately,
we don't live in that world.

1192
01:26:55,360 --> 01:26:56,800
Funny...

1193
01:26:57,800 --> 01:27:01,119
...I always believed that the world
is what we make of it.

1194
01:27:02,720 --> 01:27:05,759
Excuse me, Dr. Drumlin, sir?

1195
01:27:07,320 --> 01:27:08,799
Good luck on the test.

1196
01:27:09,039 --> 01:27:11,278
- The pad leader has issued the order...
- Thank you.

1197
01:27:11,440 --> 01:27:14,479
...to clear the pad of all nonessential...
- Right this way, sir.

1198
01:27:18,799 --> 01:27:22,518
Test director, everything looks good
up here. We're ready to go.

1199
01:27:22,679 --> 01:27:25,558
All right, people, I want
things double and triple checked here.

1200
01:27:25,719 --> 01:27:29,158
We only get one shot at this.
Let's get it right.

1201
01:27:29,318 --> 01:27:32,277
Ladies and gentlemen,
we are ready for startup.

1202
01:27:32,478 --> 01:27:35,677
All controllers, I need a go-no-go
for test initiation.

1203
01:27:35,838 --> 01:27:36,797
- Mechanical?
- Go.

1204
01:27:36,958 --> 01:27:37,956
- Electrical?
- Go.

1205
01:27:38,117 --> 01:27:39,157
- Dynamics?
- Go.

1206
01:27:39,318 --> 01:27:40,557
- Communications?
- Go.

1207
01:27:40,717 --> 01:27:41,716
- Pod systems?
- Go

1208
01:27:41,877 --> 01:27:43,356
- Safety?
- Go.

1209
01:27:43,517 --> 01:27:46,317
Crew Ops, verify all pre-test
procedures are complete.

1210
01:27:46,477 --> 01:27:47,836
Yes, verified. I'm go.

1211
01:27:47,997 --> 01:27:50,396
Pad leader, we are good.
Is everything okay with you?

1212
01:27:50,557 --> 01:27:53,116
Roger. The pad is a go.

1213
01:27:53,277 --> 01:27:55,996
Test initiation, on my mark.

1214
01:27:56,437 --> 01:27:57,755
Five...

1215
01:27:57,916 --> 01:27:59,115
...four...

1216
01:27:59,276 --> 01:28:00,515
...three...

1217
01:28:00,676 --> 01:28:01,835
...two...

1218
01:28:02,236 --> 01:28:03,675
...one.

1219
01:28:03,836 --> 01:28:05,195
Mark.

1220
01:28:05,356 --> 01:28:07,034
- Test start.
- Rings are unlocked.

1221
01:28:07,195 --> 01:28:08,875
Power levels indicate a good start.

1222
01:28:09,036 --> 01:28:11,794
We have begun the full-scale
test of Earth's first system...

1223
01:28:11,955 --> 01:28:15,353
...built by the sharing of knowledge
with a neighbor in our universe.

1224
01:28:15,515 --> 01:28:17,673
All power sources on core induction bus.

1225
01:28:17,834 --> 01:28:19,393
IPV power transfer.

1226
01:28:19,554 --> 01:28:23,153
Ring motion detect.
Alpha, Bravo, Charlie.

1227
01:28:24,154 --> 01:28:27,072
- Gerry, how are we looking?
- Looks good. We're underway.

1228
01:28:27,233 --> 01:28:28,912
Looks like we have a normal startup.

1229
01:28:29,073 --> 01:28:31,512
Roger, David.
It's looking good here.

1230
01:28:36,913 --> 01:28:39,912
We are moments away from
the initiation of the drop sequence.

1231
01:28:40,073 --> 01:28:41,992
All systems are go.

1232
01:28:44,033 --> 01:28:46,551
- Mechanical, you still happy?
- Roger that.

1233
01:28:46,712 --> 01:28:50,031
I'll tell you, this is very exciting
from up here.

1234
01:28:52,112 --> 01:28:55,590
- We've got 4 percent.
- We're confirming 4 percent.

1235
01:28:56,792 --> 01:28:59,990
Frequency 9.85.

1236
01:29:00,151 --> 01:29:05,670
Harmonics in the green.
G-level 1.1.

1237
01:29:05,831 --> 01:29:09,029
- Five percent.
- Confirmed. We are at 5 percent.

1238
01:29:09,190 --> 01:29:10,869
David, how's it looking to you?

1239
01:29:11,031 --> 01:29:13,749
Okay. I'm gonna take a look
and show you what we got.

1240
01:29:13,910 --> 01:29:15,989
All test-subject instrumentation
looks good.

1241
01:29:16,150 --> 01:29:19,669
Confirmed, we have a good picture
from Dr. Drumlirs PRD.

1242
01:29:19,830 --> 01:29:22,188
Hope you guys are seeing
what I'm seeing.

1243
01:29:22,550 --> 01:29:24,388
All systems are go.

1244
01:29:25,909 --> 01:29:27,428
This is really something.

1245
01:29:27,629 --> 01:29:29,228
For purposes of this test...

1246
01:29:29,389 --> 01:29:33,427
...Dr. Drumlin will be on top of
the gantry crane that's over the Machine.

1247
01:29:33,588 --> 01:29:35,667
We've got some video animation...

1248
01:29:35,828 --> 01:29:39,186
...to show you just how this machine,
it is thought, will work.

1249
01:29:39,347 --> 01:29:40,947
The passenger pod will be released.

1250
01:29:41,147 --> 01:29:45,306
It will come down through the center of
the rings and into the Machine's core.

1251
01:29:45,467 --> 01:29:49,386
The big question everyone here is asking is,
of course, what happens then?

1252
01:29:49,547 --> 01:29:54,185
Some believe that the rings function as
some sort of an accelerator or something...

1253
01:29:54,347 --> 01:29:56,866
...sending its energy
into this passenger pod...

1254
01:29:57,026 --> 01:29:59,625
...making it rocket away
at near the speed of light.

1255
01:29:59,826 --> 01:30:04,265
Other people believe it might open up
a doorway to some other dimension.

1256
01:30:04,425 --> 01:30:07,744
Who's right?
Well, that's what today's test is all about.

1257
01:30:08,346 --> 01:30:10,705
- Thirty-five percent.
- Subsystems, are you ready?

1258
01:30:10,865 --> 01:30:13,904
- Forty percent normal acceleration.
- Roger, confirm 40 percent.

1259
01:30:14,105 --> 01:30:16,944
All controllers stand by
to initiate drop sequence...

1260
01:30:17,105 --> 01:30:18,624
...on my mark.

1261
01:30:18,785 --> 01:30:21,023
All systems ready for drop sequence.

1262
01:30:21,184 --> 01:30:23,343
Forty-five percent.

1263
01:30:23,504 --> 01:30:25,583
We're reading 45 percent.

1264
01:30:26,544 --> 01:30:28,463
Can you verify closure?

1265
01:30:29,704 --> 01:30:31,183
Forty-six.

1266
01:30:31,344 --> 01:30:35,822
All controllers stand by
to initiate IPV drop sequence. On my mark.

1267
01:30:36,464 --> 01:30:38,143
Forty-eight percent.

1268
01:30:38,743 --> 01:30:41,062
Test djrector,
I'm feeling a very strange vibration.

1269
01:30:41,223 --> 01:30:42,383
Are you feeling it down there?

1270
01:30:42,543 --> 01:30:44,422
Gerry, can you confirm any vibration?

1271
01:30:44,943 --> 01:30:46,702
Negative, everything looks good here.

1272
01:30:46,863 --> 01:30:48,782
- Crew Ops?
- Nothing wrong with Elmer.

1273
01:30:48,943 --> 01:30:50,702
We're not seeing anything abnormal.

1274
01:30:50,863 --> 01:30:53,540
No good. Hold the sequence.
I'm gonna take a direct reading.

1275
01:30:54,022 --> 01:30:57,260
- What the hell is he talking about?
- Can anyone say grandstanding?

1276
01:30:57,421 --> 01:30:59,340
He sure knows he's on TV!

1277
01:30:59,501 --> 01:31:02,500
Back home that's what we call
an overcooked ham.

1278
01:31:02,661 --> 01:31:05,060
I'm reading 10 kilohertz!

1279
01:31:05,221 --> 01:31:07,900
What's your reading on the first
and second order G-levels?

1280
01:31:08,100 --> 01:31:09,899
G-levels are right on.

1281
01:31:10,380 --> 01:31:13,739
We confirm Drumlirs readings
and they're all normal. We're go.

1282
01:31:13,900 --> 01:31:15,339
Copy that, Dynamics.

1283
01:31:15,500 --> 01:31:18,139
I think we're okay,
but we'll let him finish.

1284
01:31:19,299 --> 01:31:21,259
- Mechanical, you still okay?
- Roger, chief.

1285
01:31:21,420 --> 01:31:22,699
We're right on the money.

1286
01:31:22,859 --> 01:31:25,058
We've got a security problem here.

1287
01:31:25,219 --> 01:31:26,738
Ellie, are you sure?

1288
01:31:26,899 --> 01:31:29,098
Yeah. This guy, he shouldn't be there.
I know him.

1289
01:31:29,259 --> 01:31:32,098
Gerry, execute the
rapid shutdown sequence.

1290
01:31:32,259 --> 01:31:35,418
Security, move emergency
response team into position one.

1291
01:31:35,579 --> 01:31:38,058
- Get me Drumlin on a secure loop, please.
- You got him.

1292
01:31:38,218 --> 01:31:41,577
- David, can you hear me?
- Yes, I hear.

1293
01:31:41,738 --> 01:31:43,937
All right, we've got
a security breach here.

1294
01:31:44,298 --> 01:31:46,217
Right behind you.
The tall guy.

1295
01:31:46,698 --> 01:31:49,817
The technician. See him?

1296
01:31:51,778 --> 01:31:54,056
He's not supposed to be there.

1297
01:31:58,537 --> 01:32:01,096
David, he's got something in his hand!

1298
01:32:01,256 --> 01:32:03,696
Him! Take him!
Security breach!

1299
01:32:04,337 --> 01:32:05,416
He's got a bomb!

1300
01:32:05,577 --> 01:32:08,096
I want that emergency-response
team up on the gantry now.

1301
01:32:08,256 --> 01:32:09,856
Security, stage one alert.

1302
01:32:10,017 --> 01:32:14,334
By God, move all the fire and
rescue personnel into position one.

1303
01:32:49,412 --> 01:32:51,451
All right, all right, back to your stations.

1304
01:32:51,612 --> 01:32:54,611
I need you to be professional, people.
Settle down.

1305
01:32:54,812 --> 01:32:57,571
Pad leader, pad leader, do you copy?

1306
01:33:14,291 --> 01:33:16,850
The scene earlier today,
when David Drumlin...

1307
01:33:17,051 --> 01:33:18,690
...advisor to two presidents...

1308
01:33:18,851 --> 01:33:22,690
...and winner of the National Academy
of Sciences lifetime award...

1309
01:33:22,850 --> 01:33:26,489
...was laid to rest
at Arlington National Cemetery.

1310
01:33:30,050 --> 01:33:31,889
In a related story, last night's raid...

1311
01:33:32,049 --> 01:33:33,528
Can I help you?

1312
01:33:33,688 --> 01:33:37,567
- Oh, you're... I've got some mail for you.
...resulted in the discovery of this video.

1313
01:33:37,728 --> 01:33:42,247
The suicide note of the leader of the
terrorist group now believed responsible...

1314
01:33:42,408 --> 01:33:44,847
...for the explosion in Florida this week.

1315
01:33:45,008 --> 01:33:49,807
What we do,
we do for the goodness of all mankind.

1316
01:33:50,447 --> 01:33:53,247
This won't be understood, not now...

1317
01:33:53,408 --> 01:33:55,286
...but the apocalypse to come...

1318
01:33:56,407 --> 01:33:58,486
...will vindicate our faith.

1319
01:34:21,806 --> 01:34:23,565
Welcome home.

1320
01:35:26,640 --> 01:35:28,919
Oh, Comrade Arroway...

1321
01:35:29,080 --> 01:35:32,239
...he has been expecting your call.
One moment, please.

1322
01:35:41,599 --> 01:35:42,758
Mr. Hadden?

1323
01:35:43,359 --> 01:35:44,637
Doctor.

1324
01:35:45,719 --> 01:35:47,438
How kind of you to call.

1325
01:35:48,118 --> 01:35:50,437
Mr. Hadden, where are you?

1326
01:35:52,078 --> 01:35:56,557
The Russian government was kind enough
to give me accommodations on Mir.

1327
01:35:57,358 --> 01:35:59,157
You're living on a space station?

1328
01:36:00,598 --> 01:36:02,837
It's quite simple, really.

1329
01:36:03,837 --> 01:36:07,276
The low-oxygen,
zero-gravity environment...

1330
01:36:07,437 --> 01:36:11,956
...is the only thing keeping
the cancer from eating me alive.

1331
01:36:13,435 --> 01:36:16,035
Actually, I quite like it up here.

1332
01:36:16,475 --> 01:36:20,115
My little room has one hell of a view.

1333
01:36:26,995 --> 01:36:29,394
I wanna show you something.

1334
01:36:33,395 --> 01:36:35,754
Hokkaido Island.

1335
01:36:36,634 --> 01:36:38,914
The systems integration site.

1336
01:36:39,874 --> 01:36:42,033
Look closer.

1337
01:36:49,354 --> 01:36:52,832
First rule in government spending:

1338
01:36:52,993 --> 01:36:56,752
Why build one when you can have
two at twice the price?

1339
01:36:56,913 --> 01:37:00,552
Only, this one can be kept secret.

1340
01:37:00,713 --> 01:37:02,671
Controlled by Americans...

1341
01:37:02,832 --> 01:37:06,311
...built by the Japanese subcontractors...

1342
01:37:06,992 --> 01:37:10,431
...who also happen to be...

1343
01:37:10,592 --> 01:37:12,591
...recently acquired...

1344
01:37:12,752 --> 01:37:15,751
...wholly-owned subsidiaries...

1345
01:37:15,912 --> 01:37:18,190
...of Hadden Industries.
- Of Hadden Industries.

1346
01:37:21,231 --> 01:37:24,270
They still want
an American to go, doctor.

1347
01:37:27,751 --> 01:37:29,990
Wanna take a ride?

1348
01:38:10,387 --> 01:38:14,506
And augmenting our restraint and
communications console subsystem...

1349
01:38:14,666 --> 01:38:16,585
...we have your personal recording unit.

1350
01:38:16,746 --> 01:38:20,705
Normal, infrared and ultraviolet lenses.

1351
01:38:20,866 --> 01:38:24,745
Digital microchip good for
thousands of hours of recording.

1352
01:38:25,905 --> 01:38:27,905
Okay, look, I understand...

1353
01:38:28,066 --> 01:38:31,345
...the reason for recording
and documenting the mission.

1354
01:38:31,506 --> 01:38:34,225
But I just... I wanna go on record
one more time.

1355
01:38:34,386 --> 01:38:37,744
The transmitted specs
never said anything about any chair...

1356
01:38:37,985 --> 01:38:42,304
...or a restraining harness or survival gear.

1357
01:38:42,465 --> 01:38:44,224
Why can't we just trust the original...?

1358
01:38:44,385 --> 01:38:48,344
Doctor, both the IMC Board
and the SI team reviewed the matter...

1359
01:38:48,544 --> 01:38:52,143
...and concluded that
the design impact is negligible.

1360
01:38:52,304 --> 01:38:53,942
Bottom line is...

1361
01:38:54,103 --> 01:38:56,342
...we're not putting anybody
aboard this machine...

1362
01:38:56,543 --> 01:38:59,422
...unless there is
some sort of minimal protection.

1363
01:38:59,583 --> 01:39:01,382
End of story.

1364
01:39:03,703 --> 01:39:06,821
- Okay.
- Ellie...

1365
01:39:07,662 --> 01:39:11,581
...we've been giving these to the astronauts
since the beginning of the space program.

1366
01:39:12,862 --> 01:39:15,061
It's never been made public, of course.

1367
01:39:15,262 --> 01:39:17,261
It's fast and it's painless.

1368
01:39:19,902 --> 01:39:22,661
I'm gonna travel 26 light years
to commit suicide?

1369
01:39:22,821 --> 01:39:24,940
Something may go wrong.

1370
01:39:25,101 --> 01:39:27,740
There may be
an unforeseen mechanical failure.

1371
01:39:28,460 --> 01:39:31,420
You could be marooned, unable to return.

1372
01:39:32,541 --> 01:39:35,540
There are a thousand reasons
we can think of for you to have this...

1373
01:39:35,740 --> 01:39:38,779
...but mostly it's for the reasons
we can't think of.

1374
01:40:03,978 --> 01:40:05,057
Come in.

1375
01:40:06,538 --> 01:40:10,377
- Dr. Arroway, time to get ready.
- Thank you.

1376
01:40:20,616 --> 01:40:22,255
I know you don't have much time.

1377
01:40:22,416 --> 01:40:25,375
As soon as I found out about the Machine,
I called the president.

1378
01:40:25,576 --> 01:40:27,575
I came with Kitz.

1379
01:40:27,736 --> 01:40:29,935
I had to see you one more time.

1380
01:40:30,096 --> 01:40:31,775
- Oh, God, I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

1381
01:40:31,935 --> 01:40:33,734
No, I'm glad you came.

1382
01:40:33,895 --> 01:40:36,654
There's something I gotta say to you.

1383
01:40:37,495 --> 01:40:41,574
The reason I didn't vote for you to go was
a good reason, but it wasrt the real one.

1384
01:40:42,615 --> 01:40:44,534
I didn't vote for you to go...

1385
01:40:46,015 --> 01:40:48,094
...because I don't wanna lose you.

1386
01:40:49,094 --> 01:40:51,813
You find your way home, all right?

1387
01:41:07,533 --> 01:41:08,892
Twenty-three hours ago...

1388
01:41:09,053 --> 01:41:12,931
...the world was stunned by the
announcement of a second Machine...

1389
01:41:13,092 --> 01:41:16,091
...and its passenger,
Eleanor Ann Arroway.

1390
01:41:16,292 --> 01:41:19,731
Now the question
that's on everyone's mind:

1391
01:41:19,892 --> 01:41:21,811
Will history repeat itself?

1392
01:41:21,972 --> 01:41:24,171
With a piece of engineering
this complex...

1393
01:41:24,332 --> 01:41:28,251
...with so many unknowns,
could the unthinkable occur?

1394
01:41:28,412 --> 01:41:31,730
The security in Hokkaido
has been incredibly tight.

1395
01:41:31,891 --> 01:41:35,089
No reporters whatsoever
have been allowed near the site.

1396
01:43:51,240 --> 01:43:53,159
Thanks.

1397
01:44:09,039 --> 01:44:11,917
Magnetic restraint is secure.
All life support functions normal.

1398
01:44:12,119 --> 01:44:15,157
Roger that. Ellie, this is Control.
Do you copy?

1399
01:44:15,317 --> 01:44:17,556
Ellie to Control, reading you five-by-five.

1400
01:44:17,717 --> 01:44:21,636
- Comm 1, Give me Ellie's PRD.
- Video unit recording and transmitting.

1401
01:44:22,557 --> 01:44:24,996
- Are you reading me?
- That's affirmative.

1402
01:44:25,157 --> 01:44:27,356
Video looks good.

1403
01:44:27,517 --> 01:44:29,956
- Copy that, Control.
- Okay.

1404
01:44:30,117 --> 01:44:32,875
Ellie, we're gonna proceed
to button you up.

1405
01:44:33,036 --> 01:44:35,595
Roger, Control. I'm ready.

1406
01:44:38,876 --> 01:44:41,155
- Dynamics...
- I can confirm the walkway retraction.

1407
01:44:41,316 --> 01:44:42,275
- Systems?
- Go.

1408
01:44:42,436 --> 01:44:43,754
- Communications?
- Go.

1409
01:44:43,916 --> 01:44:45,514
- Life support?
- Go.

1410
01:44:45,675 --> 01:44:47,874
Ellie, we are go for closure.

1411
01:44:49,275 --> 01:44:51,074
I'm go here.

1412
01:44:51,915 --> 01:44:55,274
Mechanical, initiate
IPV closure sequence.

1413
01:44:56,835 --> 01:44:58,953
Hold on, let me get you a chair.

1414
01:44:59,634 --> 01:45:00,633
I'm go.

1415
01:45:00,794 --> 01:45:04,513
- It's nice to smell you again, Mr. Kitz.
- You too.

1416
01:45:04,674 --> 01:45:06,433
Wouldrt peg him as a Polo man.

1417
01:45:15,593 --> 01:45:16,873
I got a visual on the door.

1418
01:45:17,033 --> 01:45:18,912
IPV escape system is armed.

1419
01:45:19,074 --> 01:45:20,992
Door is looking good.

1420
01:45:25,993 --> 01:45:27,591
Door alignment looks good.

1421
01:45:55,029 --> 01:45:57,029
Ellie, we are showing green
across the board.

1422
01:45:57,190 --> 01:46:00,388
Copy that, Control. IPV is secure.

1423
01:46:07,228 --> 01:46:09,147
We are at 30 percent.

1424
01:46:09,308 --> 01:46:10,547
Copy that, 30 percent.

1425
01:46:15,228 --> 01:46:17,787
- How you doing in there, EI?
- Kent?

1426
01:46:18,508 --> 01:46:21,187
- Is that you?
- That's a big affirmative.

1427
01:46:22,068 --> 01:46:23,587
Who let you in there, huh?

1428
01:46:23,748 --> 01:46:25,787
A higher power intervened.

1429
01:46:27,748 --> 01:46:29,026
Well, I'm glad you came.

1430
01:46:33,587 --> 01:46:34,706
Thirty-five percent.

1431
01:46:35,427 --> 01:46:36,866
Copy that, 35 percent.

1432
01:46:37,027 --> 01:46:38,306
- Mechanical?
- We're good.

1433
01:46:38,467 --> 01:46:39,745
Forty percent.

1434
01:46:43,227 --> 01:46:45,026
I'm picking up a moderate vibration here.

1435
01:46:46,147 --> 01:46:49,625
- Dynamics, can you confirm vibration?
- Everything looks good here.

1436
01:46:49,826 --> 01:46:52,945
She's feeling the same thing
they felt at the Cape at this point.

1437
01:46:53,106 --> 01:46:54,625
Ellie, the vibration is normal.

