tends to be the right one.

1688
02:07:11,128 --> 02:07:12,607
Exactly.

1689
02:07:12,768 --> 02:07:15,127
Now, you tell me.
What is more likely here?

1690
02:07:15,287 --> 02:07:18,606
That a message from aliens
results in a magical machine...

1691
02:07:18,767 --> 02:07:21,366
...that whisks you away
to the center of the galaxy...

1692
02:07:21,567 --> 02:07:24,325
...to go windsurfing with your dad
and a split second later...

1693
02:07:24,486 --> 02:07:27,805
...returns you home
without a single shred of proof?

1694
02:07:27,967 --> 02:07:31,605
Or that your experience
is the result of being...

1695
02:07:31,766 --> 02:07:36,045
...the unwitting star in the farewell
performance of one S.R. Hadden?

1696
02:07:36,206 --> 02:07:39,844
A man with the means, motive and
opportunity to play you and the rest of us...

1697
02:07:40,086 --> 02:07:44,124
...as pawns in the biggest, most elaborate,
most expensive hoax of all time?

1698
02:07:45,365 --> 02:07:47,205
Dr. Arroway.

1699
02:07:49,006 --> 02:07:53,204
You come to us with no evidence,
no record...

1700
02:07:53,365 --> 02:07:55,084
...no artifacts.

1701
02:07:55,245 --> 02:07:59,244
Only a story that, to put it mildly,
strains credibility.

1702
02:08:00,324 --> 02:08:03,323
Over half a trillion dollars were spent.

1703
02:08:03,484 --> 02:08:06,363
Dozens of lives were lost.

1704
02:08:06,964 --> 02:08:11,483
Are you really gonna sit there
and tell us we should just take this all...

1705
02:08:12,203 --> 02:08:13,683
...on faith?

1706
02:08:17,524 --> 02:08:19,642
Please answer the question, doctor.

1707
02:08:23,402 --> 02:08:25,401
Is it possible that it didn't happen?

1708
02:08:25,562 --> 02:08:26,681
Yes.

1709
02:08:29,442 --> 02:08:32,440
As a scientist I must concede that.
I must volunteer that.

1710
02:08:36,600 --> 02:08:38,440
Wait a minute, let me get this straight.

1711
02:08:38,601 --> 02:08:42,320
You admit you have absolutely no
physical evidence to back up your story?

1712
02:08:42,640 --> 02:08:43,639
Yes.

1713
02:08:43,800 --> 02:08:46,720
You admit that you very well may have
hallucinated this whole thing?

1714
02:08:46,880 --> 02:08:49,559
- Yes.
- You admit that if you were in our position...

1715
02:08:49,720 --> 02:08:53,319
...you would respond with exactly the same
degree of incredulity and skepticism?

1716
02:08:53,479 --> 02:08:54,679
Yes.

1717
02:08:54,839 --> 02:08:57,679
Then why don't you simply withdraw
your testimony and concede...

1718
02:08:57,840 --> 02:09:02,798
...that this journey to the center of
the galaxy in fact never took place?

1719
02:09:05,679 --> 02:09:07,597
Because I can't.

1720
02:09:13,879 --> 02:09:17,397
I had an experience.

1721
02:09:18,998 --> 02:09:21,477
I can't prove it.
I can't even explain it.

1722
02:09:21,638 --> 02:09:24,596
But everything that I know as
a human being, everything I am...

1723
02:09:24,757 --> 02:09:26,796
...tells me it was real.

1724
02:09:28,757 --> 02:09:32,476
I was given something wonderful,
something that changed me forever.

1725
02:09:32,637 --> 02:09:34,116
A vision...

1726
02:09:34,277 --> 02:09:36,276
...of the universe...

1727
02:09:36,437 --> 02:09:38,995
...that tells us undeniably...

1728
02:09:39,156 --> 02:09:41,315
...how tiny and insignificant...

1729
02:09:41,475 --> 02:09:45,034
...and how rare and precious we all are.

1730
02:09:46,155 --> 02:09:48,474
A vision that tells us
that we belong to something...

1731
02:09:48,635 --> 02:09:54,073
...that is greater than ourselves,
that we are not... That none of us are alone.

1732
02:09:58,514 --> 02:10:02,353
I wish I could share that.

1733
02:10:04,754 --> 02:10:05,872
I wish...

1734
02:10:07,274 --> 02:10:11,153
...that everyone,
if even for one moment...

1735
02:10:11,314 --> 02:10:16,833
...could feel that awe
and humility and hope.

1736
02:10:17,233 --> 02:10:19,152
But...

1737
02:10:25,072 --> 02:10:27,271
That continues to be my wish.

1738
02:11:06,749 --> 02:11:09,947
Dr. Arroway, get a picture, please?
Get a photo over here?

1739
02:11:11,509 --> 02:11:13,067
Here comes Ellie.

1740
02:11:47,866 --> 02:11:50,665
Reverend Joss! Reverend Joss!

1741
02:11:50,826 --> 02:11:54,064
Reverend Joss, what do you believe?
What do you believe?

1742
02:11:58,146 --> 02:12:01,984
As a person of faith, I'm bound by
a different covenant than Dr. Arroway.

1743
02:12:03,664 --> 02:12:05,824
But our goal is one and the same.

1744
02:12:06,304 --> 02:12:07,864
The pursuit of truth.

1745
02:12:11,264 --> 02:12:12,503
I, for one, believe her.

1746
02:12:35,102 --> 02:12:37,861
So, what happens now?
We give her a medal?

1747
02:12:38,022 --> 02:12:40,781
I'd say at least a healthy grant.

1748
02:12:40,942 --> 02:12:44,260
I assume you read the confidential report
from the investigating committee?

1749
02:12:44,461 --> 02:12:46,140
I flipped through it.

1750
02:12:46,301 --> 02:12:50,340
I was especially interested
in the section on Arroway's video unit.

1751
02:12:51,101 --> 02:12:53,339
The one that recorded the static.

1752
02:12:54,540 --> 02:12:56,180
Continue.

1753
02:12:56,780 --> 02:13:00,459
The fact that it recorded static
isn't what interests me.

1754
02:13:05,099 --> 02:13:06,419
Continue.

1755
02:13:07,260 --> 02:13:09,019
What interests me...

1756
02:13:09,180 --> 02:13:12,858
...is that it recorded
approximately 18 hours of it.

1757
02:13:17,899 --> 02:13:19,738
That is interesting, isn't it?

1758
02:13:26,138 --> 02:13:29,817
You can see over there,
we're building 45 brand-new dishes.

1759
02:13:29,978 --> 02:13:33,777
And that means when you put them
together with all the radio telescopes...

1760
02:13:33,938 --> 02:13:35,377
...all over the world...

1761
02:13:35,538 --> 02:13:40,017
...then we get to hear farther into space
than anybody has ever heard before.

1762
02:13:40,178 --> 02:13:41,175
Yeah.

1763
02:13:41,336 --> 02:13:44,055
Are there other people
out there in the universe?

1764
02:13:45,056 --> 02:13:47,695
That's a good question.
What do you think, huh?

1765
02:13:48,256 --> 02:13:51,454
- I don't know.
- That's a good answer.

1766
02:13:52,295 --> 02:13:53,295
Skeptic, huh?

1767
02:13:54,535 --> 02:13:59,214
The important thing is that you all
keep searching for your own answers.

1768
02:13:59,375 --> 02:14:02,094
I'll tell you one thing
about the universe, though.

1769
02:14:02,255 --> 02:14:05,974
The universe is a pretty big place.

1770
02:14:06,935 --> 02:14:12,213
It's bigger than anything
anyone has ever dreamed of before.

1771
02:14:13,734 --> 02:14:15,333
So if it's just us...

1772
02:14:16,894 --> 02:14:19,572
...it seems like an awful waste of space.

1773
02:14:21,014 --> 02:14:22,332
Right?
